fields.value: Contextuality in a psychophysical double-identification experiment

dsDescriptionValue.value: This is the complete set of data obtained in the experiment described in "True Contextuality in a Psychophysical Experiment," arXiv:1812.00105 [q-bio.NC].

publicationCitation.value: True Contextuality in a Psychophysical Experiment," by Victor Cervantes and Ehtibar Dzhafarov

files.description:
The file includes only experimental sessions data (no training data).

Participant.code: Code assigned to the participant: P1, P2, or P3
Session: File name for the experimental session data. Identified by participant code, date and time when the session was completed.
Trial: Index of the trial in the session. Starts at 0 and runs consecutively to the number of trials minus one.
leftCircle: Location of the dot shown in the left circle.
rightCircle: Location of the dot shown in the right circle.
leftResponse: Response given by the participant for the location of the dot shown in the left circle.
rightResponse: Response given by the participant for the location of the dot shown in the right circle.
RT: Response time in seconds from the moment the dots are shown on the screen until both responses were given (not used in the analysis).
